## NEW HELPERS & HANDLERS IN nodes.py

### `_get_cell(row, *candidates)`
Case-insensitive cell lookup. Maps all row keys to lowercase, then looks up each candidate.

### `_validate_creator_row(row)`
Validates 8 columns: Employee ID, Project ID, Product ID, Task Index, Activity Index, Start Date, End Date, Planned Hours. Returns (fields_dict, error_string).

### `_validate_reviewer_row(row)`
Validates 4 columns: Task ID, Date, Hours, Remark. Returns (fields_dict, error_string).

### `_validate_approver_row(row)`
Validates 1 column: Worklog ID. Returns (fields_dict, error_string).

### `_handle_creator_excel(state, uploaded_files, current_emp_no, execution_log)`
Processes creator Excel rows via `timesheet_store.create_task()`. Sets `created_by=current_emp_no` from server-side, never from Excel.

### `_handle_reviewer_excel(state, uploaded_files, current_emp_no, execution_log)`
Processes reviewer Excel rows via `timesheet_store.add_worklog()`. Sets `resource_id=int(current_emp_no)` from server-side.

### `_handle_approver_excel(state, uploaded_files, current_emp_no, execution_log)`
Processes approver Excel rows via `timesheet_store.approve_worklog()` with decision="APPROVED".

